s-new}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Minister Resident]] in Northwest Africa|years=1942\u20131945}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Harold Balfour, 1st Baron Balfour of Inchrye|Harold Balfour]]}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[E. F. L. Wood, 1st Earl of Halifax|The Earl of Halifax]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Chancellors of the University of Oxford|Chancellor of the University of Oxford]]|years=1960\u20131986}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Roy Jenkins]]}}\n{{s-ach|rec}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Clement Attlee|The Earl Attlee]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Oldest living Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]]|years=1967\u20131986}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Alec Douglas-Home|The Lord Home of the Hirsel]]}}\n{{s-reg|uk}}\n{{s-new|creation}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Earl of Stockton]]<br />[[Viscount Macmillan of Ovenden]]|years=1984\u20131986}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Alexander Macmillan, 2nd Earl of Stockton|Alexander Macmillan]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Navboxes|title= Harold Macmillan navigational boxes |list=\n{{Harold Macmillan}}\n{{UKPrimeMinisters}}\n{{British Chancellors of the Exchequer}}\n{{Foreign Secretary}}\n{{Secretary of State for Defence}}\n{{UK Conservative Party}}\n{{Third Churchill Ministry}}\n{{Churchill Caretaker Ministry}}\n{{Chancellors of the University of Oxford}}\n{{Profumo Affair}}\n}}\n{{Portal bar|United Kingdom|War}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Macmillan, Harold}}\n[[Category:1894 births]]\n[[Category:1986 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century Prime Ministers of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:British Army personnel of World War I]]\n[[Category:British Secretaries of State for Foreign Affairs]]\n[[Category:British Secretaries of State]]\n[[Category:British book publishers (people)]]\n[[Category:Burials in Sussex]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the Exchequer of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party Prime Ministers of the United Kingdom]]\n[