isher = Weidenfeld & Nicolson| isbn = 978-0-753-82702-4 | ref = harv }}\n\n==Further reading==\n* ''The Guardsmen: Harold Macmillan, Three Friends and the World They Made'' by Simon Ball, Harper Perennial, London 2005. {{ISBN|978-0-00-653163-0}}\n* ''An English Affair: Sex, Class and Power in the Age of Profumo'' by [[Richard Davenport-Hines]], HarperCollins, London 2013. {{ISBN|978-0-00-743585-2}}\n* ''Eisenhower, Macmillan and Allied Unity 1957\u201361'' by Anthony O. Edmonds / E. Bruce Geelhoed, Palgrave Macmillan, Basingstoke 2003. {{ISBN|0-333-64227-9}}.\n* ''Having It So Good: Britain In The Fifties'' by [[Peter Hennessy, Baron Hennessy of Nympsfield|Peter Hennessy]], Penguin Books, London 2006. {{ISBN|978-0-14-100409-9}}.\n* ''Macmillan : Portrait of a Politician'', by [[Emrys Hughes]], [[Allen & Unwin]], 1962. {{ISBN|978-0-04-923013-2}}\n* ''The Last Edwardian at No.10: An Impression of Harold Macmillan'', by George Hutchinson, Quartet Books, London 1980. {{ISBN|978-0-7043-2232-5}}.\n* ''Macmillan A Publishing Tradition'' by Elizabeth James, London 2002. {{ISBN|0-333-73517-X}}\n* ''[[The Minister and the Massacres]]'', by Nikolai Tolstoy, London, 1986, {{ISBN|0-09-164010-5}}\n* [http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9049827/Harold-Macmillan Britannica Online about Harold Macmillan]\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Harold Macmillan}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Wikisource author}}\n\n* [http://alsos.wlu.edu/qsearch.aspx?browse=people/Macmillian,+Harold Annotated Bibliography for Harold Macmillan from the Alsos Digital Library for Nuclear Issues]\n* {{hansard-contribs | mr-harold-macmillan | Harold Macmillan }}\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/december/29/newsid_2547000/2547307.stm BBC Harold Macmillan obituary]\n* President of the friends of Roquetaillade association [http://www.roquetaillade.eu]\n* [http://www.depauw.edu/news/index.asp?id=20586 8 June 1958 speech on \"Interdependence\" at DePauw University]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070515190448/http://www.pm.gov.uk/output/Page131.asp More about Harold Macmillan] on the Downing Street website\n* [http://www.depauw.edu/news/?id=27045 1968&nbsp;\u2013 Britain's Harold Macmillan Makes Return Visit to DePauw, Calls for New Rapprochement]\n* [http://www.rootsandleaves.com/ RootsAndLeaves.com], Cavendish family genealogy\n* [http://www.bodley.ox.ac.uk/dept/scwmss/projects/suez/suez.html Bodleian Library Suez Crisis Fiftieth Anniversary Exhibition]\n* {{NPG name|name=Harold Macmillan, 1st Earl of Stockton}}\n* {{UK National Archives ID}}\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/011827}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|uk}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Robert Strother Stewart]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of Parliament for [[Stockton-on-Tees (UK Parliament constituency)|Stockton-on-Tees]]|years=[[1924 United Kingdom general election|1924]]\u2013[[1929 United Kingdom general election|1929]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Frederick Fox Riley]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Frederick Fox Riley]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of Parliament for [[Stockton-on-Tees (UK Parliament constituency)|Stockton-on-Tees]]|years=[[1931 United Kingdom general election|1931]]\u2013[[1945 United Kingdom general election|1945]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[George Chetwynd]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Sir Edward Campbell, 1st Baronet|Sir Edward Campbell]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of Parliament for [[Bromley (UK Parliament constituency)|Bromley]]|years=[[1945 Bromley by-election|1945]]\u2013[[1964 United Kingdom general election|1964]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[John Hunt (British politician)|John Hunt]]}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John Jestyn Llewellin, 1st Baron Llewellin|John Llewellin]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Ministry of Supply|Parliamentary Secretary to the Ministry of Supply]]|years=1940\u20131942}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Wyndham Portal, 1st Viscount Portal|The Viscount Portal]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[George Henry Hall, 1st Viscount Hall|George Henry Hall]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Under-Secretary of State for the Colonies]]|years=1942}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Edward Cavendish, 10th Duke o