rize]] laureate (d. 1955)\n*[[1878]] &ndash; [[Vincent de Moro-Giafferi]], French lawyer and politician (d. 1956)\n*[[1884]] &ndash; [[Jock Hutchison]], Scottish-American golfer (d. 1977)\n*[[1890]] &ndash; [[Ted Lewis (musician)|Ted Lewis]], American singer, clarinet player, and bandleader (d. 1971)\n*[[1891]] &ndash; [[Masti Venkatesha Iyengar]], Indian author and academic (d. 1986)\n*  1891   &ndash; [[Erich Marcks]], German general (d. 1944)\n*[[1896]] &ndash; [[Henry Allingham]], English soldier (d. 2009)<ref>{{cite web |title=Henry William Allingham, 6 June 1896 - 18 July 2009 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/radio4/entries/7e185c19-18d1-3267-a230-705aa674f52a |website=BBC |accessdate=11 January 2020 |language=en |date=19 July 2009}}</ref>\n*  1896   &ndash; [[Italo Balbo]], Italian air marshal and politician (d. 1940)\n*[[1898]] &ndash; [[Walter Abel]], American actor (d. 1987)\n*  1898   &ndash; [[Jacobus Johannes Fouch\u00e9]], South African politician, 2nd [[State President of South Africa]] (d. 1980)\n*  1898   &ndash; [[Ninette de Valois]], English ballerina, choreographer, and director (d. 2001)\n*[[1900]] &ndash; [[Manfred Sakel]], Ukrainian-American psychiatrist and physician (d. 1957)\n*[[1901]] &ndash; [[Jan Struther]], English author and hymnwriter (d. 1953)\n*  1901   &ndash; [[Sukarno]], Indonesian engineer and politician, 1st [[President of Indonesia]] (d. 1970)\n*[[1902]] &ndash; [[Jimmie Lunceford]], American saxophonist and bandleader (d. 1947)\n*[[1903]] &ndash; [[Aram Khachaturian]], [[Armenia]]n composer and conductor (d. 1978)\n*[[1903]] &ndash; [[Bakht Singh]], Indian evangelist, well-known bible teacher and preacher  (d. 2000)\n*[[1906]] &ndash; [[Max August Zorn]], German mathematician and academic (d. 1993)\n*[[1907]] &ndash; [[Bill Dickey]], American baseball player and manager (d. 1993)\n*  1907   &ndash; [[Robin Humphreys]], British scholar of Latin America (d. 1999)\n*[[1908]] &ndash; [[Giovanni Bracco]], Italian race car driver (