on]], New Zealand rugby player\n*  1954   &ndash; [[Urve Tiidus]], Estonian journalist and politician, 8th [[Ministry of Culture (Estonia)|Estonian Minister of Culture]]\n*  1954   &ndash; [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw \u017bmuda]], Polish footballer and manager\n*[[1955]] &ndash; [[Sandra Bernhard]], American actress and comedian\n*  1955   &ndash; [[Sam Simon]], American director, producer, and screenwriter (d. 2015)\n*  1955   &ndash; [[Suresh Bhardwaj]], Indian stage designer, director and theatre teacher (d. 2016)\n*  1955   &ndash; [[Lee Smolin]], American theoretical physicist\n*[[1956]] &ndash; [[Bj\u00f6rn Borg]], Swedish tennis player and fashion designer\n*  1956   &ndash; [[Dave Cusack]], English footballer and manager\n*  1956   &ndash; [[Marco Minniti]], Italian politician, [[Ministry of the Interior (Italy)|Italian Minister of the Interior]]\n*[[1957]] &ndash; [[Mike Gatting]], English cricketer, coach, and sportscaster\n*  1957   &ndash; [[Balanadarajah Iyer]], Sri Lankan poet and activist (d. 2004)\n*  1957   &ndash; [[Christian Rach]], German chef and author\n*[[1959]] &ndash; [[Jimmy Jam]], American keyboard player, songwriter, and producer \n*  1959   &ndash; [[Andrey Prokofyev]], Russian sprinter and hurdler (d. 1989)\n*  1959   &ndash; [[Dave Schultz (wrestling)|David Schultz]], American wrestler (d. 1996)\n*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Steve Vai]], American singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer \n*[[1961]] &ndash; [[Tom Araya]], Chilean-American singer-songwriter and bass player \n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Grant Fox]], New Zealand rugby player and sportscaster\n*[[1963]] &ndash; [[Eric Cantor]], American lawyer and politician\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Vincent Collet]], French former professional basketball player\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Wolfgang Drechsler]], German scholar, author, and academic\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Jason Isaacs]], English actor \n*  1963   &ndash; [[Ahmed Johnson]], American football player, wrestler, and actor\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Dariusz Kubicki]], Po