ruther]], English author and hymnwriter (d. 1953)\n*  1901   &ndash; [[Sukarno]], Indonesian engineer and politician, 1st [[President of Indonesia]] (d. 1970)\n*[[1902]] &ndash; [[Jimmie Lunceford]], American saxophonist and bandleader (d. 1947)\n*[[1903]] &ndash; [[Aram Khachaturian]], [[Armenia]]n composer and conductor (d. 1978)\n*[[1903]] &ndash; [[Bakht Singh]], Indian evangelist, well-known bible teacher and preacher  (d. 2000)\n*[[1906]] &ndash; [[Max August Zorn]], German mathematician and academic (d. 1993)\n*[[1907]] &ndash; [[Bill Dickey]], American baseball player and manager (d. 1993)\n*  1907   &ndash; [[Robin Humphreys]], British scholar of Latin America (d. 1999)\n*[[1908]] &ndash; [[Giovanni Bracco]], Italian race car driver (d. 1968)\n*[[1909]] &ndash; [[Isaiah Berlin]], Latvian-English historian and philosopher (d. 1997)\n*[[1913]] &ndash; [[Carlo L. Golino]], Italian-American author, critic, and academic (d. 1991)\n*[[1915]] &ndash; [[Vincent Persichetti]], American pianist and composer (d. 1987)\n*[[1916]] &ndash; [[Hamani Diori]], Nigerien academic and politician, 1st [[President of Niger]] (d. 1989)\n*[[1917]] &ndash; [[Kirk Kerkorian]], American businessman, founded the [[Tracinda Corporation]] (d. 2015)\n*[[1918]] &ndash; [[Edwin G. Krebs]], American biochemist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2009)\n*[[1919]] &ndash; [[Peter Carington, 6th Baron Carrington]], English army officer and politician, 6th [[Secretary General of NATO]] (d. 2018)\n*[[1923]] &ndash; [[V. C. Andrews]], American author, illustrator, and painter (d. 1986)\n*  1923   &ndash; [[Jean Pouliot]], Canadian broadcaster (d. 2004)\n*[[1925]] &ndash; [[Maxine Kumin]], American poet and author (d. 2014)\n*  1925   &ndash; [[Frank Chee Willeto]], American soldier and politician, 4th [[Vice President of the Navajo Nation]] (d. 2013)\n*[[1926]] &ndash; [[Torsten Andersson]], Swedish painter and illustrator (d. 2009)\n*  1926   &ndash; 