013 [[Leeds United A.F.C.|Leeds United]] (79)\n*Fewest goals conceded \u2013 [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] (26)\n\n==Top scorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rank\n!Scorer\n!Club\n!Goals\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Thierry Henry]]\n|Arsenal\n|align=center|30\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Alan Shearer]]\n|Newcastle United\n|align=center|22\n|-\n|rowspan=2 align=center|3\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Louis Saha]]\n|Manchester United/Fulham\n|align=center|20\n|-\n|{{flagicon|NLD}} [[Ruud van Nistelrooy]]\n|Manchester United\n|align=center|20\n|-\n|align=center|5\n|{{flagicon|FIN}} [[Mikael Forssell]]\n|Birmingham City\n|align=center|17\n|-\n|rowspan=4 align=center|6\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Nicolas Anelka]]\n|Manchester City\n|align=center|16\n|-\n|{{flagicon|COL}} [[Juan Pablo \u00c1ngel]]\n|Aston Villa\n|align=center|16\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Michael Owen]]\n|Liverpool\n|align=center|16\n|-\n|{{flagicon|NGA}} [[Yakubu (footballer)|Yakubu]]\n|Portsmouth\n|align=center|16\n|-\n|rowspan=3 align=center|10\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[James Beattie (footballer)|James Beattie]]\n|Southampton\n|align=center|14\n|-\n|{{flagicon|IRL}} [[Robbie Keane]]\n|Tottenham Hotspur\n|align=center|14\n|-\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Robert Pires]]\n|Arsenal\n|align=center|14\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===Monthly awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Month!![[Premier League Manager of the Month|Manager of the Month]]!![[Premier League Player of the Month|Player of the Month]]\n|-\n|August\n|[[Ars\u00e8ne Wenger]] (Arsenal)\n|[[Teddy Sheringham]] (Portsmouth)\n|-\n|September\n|[[Claudio Ranieri]] (Chelsea)\n|[[Frank Lampard]] (Chelsea)\n|-\n|October\n|[[Bobby Robson|Sir Bobby Robson]] (Newcastle United)\n|[[Alan Shearer]] (Newcastle United)\n|-\n|November\n|[[Sam Allardyce]] (Bolton Wanderers)\n|[[Jay-Jay Okocha]] (Bolton Wanderers)\n|-\n|December\n|[[Alex Ferguson|Sir Alex Ferguson]] (Manchester United)\n|[[Paul Scholes]] (Manchester United)\n|-\n|January\n|[[Sam Allardyce]] (Bolton Wanderers)\n|[[Thierry Henry]] (Arsenal)\n|-\n|February\n|[[Ars\u00e8ne Wenger]] (Arsenal)\n|[[Dennis Bergkamp]] (Arsenal) & [[Edu (footballer, born 1978)|Edu]] (Arsenal)\n|-\n|March\n|[[Claudio Ranieri]] (Chelsea)\n|[[Mikael Forssell]] (Birmingham City)\n|-\n|April\n|[[Harry Redknapp]] (Portsmouth)\n|[[Thierry Henry]] (Arsenal)\n|}\n\n===Annual awards===\n====LMA Manager of the Year====\nThe [[LMA Manager of the Year]] award was won by [[Ars\u00e8ne Wenger]].<ref>{{cite web |title=BreakingNews.ie \u2013 2004/05/17: Wenger gets Managers' Association award |url=http://archives.tcm.ie/breakingnews/2004/05/17/story148064.asp |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120701172842/http://archives.tcm.ie/breakingnews/2004/05/17/story148064.asp |archivedate=1 July 2012 |url-status=dead |accessdate=22 September 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n====PFA Players' Player of the Year====\nThe [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]] award for 2004 was won by [[Thierry Henry]] of Arsenal for the second successive year.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/3628905.stm | work=BBC News | title=Henry retains PFA crown | date=25 April 2004 | accessdate=21 April 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe shortlist for the PFA Players' Player of the Year award was as follows:\n*[[Steven Gerrard]] (Liverpool)\n*[[Thierry Henry]] (Arsenal)\n*[[Frank Lampard]] (Chelsea)\n*[[Jay-Jay Okocha]] (Bolton Wanderers)\n*[[Alan Shearer]] (Newcastle United)\n*[[Patrick Vieira]] (Arsenal)\n\n====PFA Young Player of the Year====\nThe [[PFA Young Player of the Year]] award was won by [[Scott Parker (footballer)|Scott Parker]] of [[Chelsea F.C.]].\n\nThe shortlist for the award was as follows:<ref>{{cite web|title=Henry leads PFA nominations &#124; BreakingNews.ie |url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2004/0415/sport/kfeycwsnsnmh/#ixzz0RsbXh2iB |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614133850/http://www.breakingnews.ie/archives/2004/0415/sport/kfeycwsnsnmh/ |archivedate=14 June 2011 |url-status=live |accessdate=22 September 2009 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n*[[Glen Johnson (English footballer)|Glen Johnson]] (Chelsea)\n*[[Scott Parker (footballer)|Scott Parker]] (Charlton Athletic/Chelsea)\n*[[Wayne Rooney]] (Everton)\n*[[John Terry]] (Chelsea)\n*[[Kolo Tour\u00e9]] (Arsenal)\n*[[Shaun Wright-Phillips]] (Manchester City)\n\n====PFA Team of the Year====\n{| role=\"presentation\" class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:180px;\"\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n{{Image label begin|image=Soccer Field Transparant.svg|width=175|font-size=87%}}\n{{Image label|x=0.45|y=1.28|scale=175|text=[[Tim Howard|<span style=\"color:#990000;\">Howard</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.74|y=1.00|scale=175|text=[[Lauren (footballer)|<span style=\"color:red;\">Lauren</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.60|y=1.11|scale=175|text=[[Sol Campbell|<span style=\"color:red;\">Campbell</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.23|y=1.11|scale=175|text=[[John Terry|<span style=\"color:blue;\">Terry</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.11|y=1.00|scale=175|text=[[Ashley Cole|<span style=\"color:red;\">Cole</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.69|y=0.57|scale=175|text=[[Frank Lampard|<span style=\"color:blue;\">Lampard</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.51|y=0.71|scale=175|text=[[Steven Gerrard|<span style=\"color:#990000;\">Gerrard</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.23|y=0.71|scale=175|text=[[Patrick Vieira|<span style=\"color:red;\">Vieira</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.11|y=0.57|scale=175|text=[[Robert Pires|<span style=\"color:red;\">Pires</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.23|y=0.31|scale=175|text=[[Thierry Henry|<span style=\"color:red;\">Henry</span>]]}}\n{{Image label|x=0.63|y=0.31|scale=175|text=[[Ruud van Nistelrooy|<span style=\"color:#990000;\">Van Nistelrooy</span>]]}}\n{{Image label end}}PFA Team of the Year\n|}\n\nGoalkeeper: [[Tim Howard]] (Manchester United)<br>Defence: [[Lauren (footballer)|Lauren]], [[Ashley Cole]], [[Sol Campbell]] (all Arsenal), [[John Terry]] (Chelsea)<br>Midfield: [[Steven Gerrard]] (Liverpool), [[Patrick Vieira]], [[Robert Pires]] (both Arsenal), [[Frank Lampard]] (Chelsea)<br>Attack: [[Thierry Henry]] (Arsenal), [[Ruud van Nistelrooy]] (Manchester United)\n\n====PFA Fans' Player of the Year====\n[[Thierry Henry]] of Arsenal was named the [[PFA Fans' Player of the Year]] for the second consecutive year. Henry was the first player to win this award twice.<ref>{{cite web |title=Thierry is the tops again \u2013 and it&#39;s a big &#39;hats off&#39; to divisional winners Darren Huckerby, Neil Moss and Lee Harper! &#124; The PFA Awards  &#124; Give Me Football |url=http://www.givemefootball.com/pfa-awards/thierry-is-the-tops-again---and-its-a-big-hats-off |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20090926193943/http://www.givemefootball.com/pfa-awards/thierry-is-the-tops-again---and-its-a-big-hats-off |archivedate=26 September 2009 |url-status=dead |accessdate=24 September 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11670_2297593,00.html | work=Sky Sports | title=Pfa Fans' Player of the Year}}</ref>\n\n====FWA Footballer of the Year====\nThe [[FWA Footballer of the Year]] award for 2004 was won by [[Thierry Henry]]. The Arsenal forward picked up a remarkable 87% of the votes.<ref>{{cite web |title=Henry named FWA player of year &#124; Article from Xinhua News Agency &#124; HighBeam Research |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-16568533.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102034500/http://www.highbeam.com/Search?searchTerm=Henry+named+FWA+player+of+year&searchType=Article&currentPage=0&orderBy= |archivedate=2 November 2012 |url-status=dead |accessdate=28 September 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n====Premier League Fair Play Award====\nThe Premier League Fair Play Award merit is given to the team who has been the most sporting and best behaved team. Champions Arsenal won this.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/Features/EnglishDomestic/Postings/2004/08/Arsenal_FairPlay.htm|archive-url=https://archive.today/20041027082515/http://www.thefa.com/Features/EnglishDomestic/Postings/2004/08/Arsenal_FairPlay.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=27 October 2004|title=TheFA.com - Fair Play to Gunners|date=27 October 2004}}</ref><ref>http://www.premierleague.com/staticFiles/0/66/0,,12306~91648,00.pdf</ref>\n\n====Behaviour of the Public League====\nGiven to the best-behaved fans, Arsenal won this, thus achieving a fair play double.<ref name=\"web.archive.org\"/>\n\n====Premier League Manager of the Year====\n[[Ars\u00e8ne Wenger]] won the [[Premier League Manager of the Season|Premier League Manager of the Year]] award. His team won 26 games, losing 0 and drawing 12 scoring 73 goals, conceding 26.<ref>{{cite web |title=BreakingNews.ie \u2013 2004/05/17: Wenger gets Managers' Association award |url=http://archives.tcm.ie/breakingnews/2004/05/17/story148064.asp |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120701172842/http://archives.tcm.ie/breakingnews/2004/05/17/story148064.asp |archivedate=1 July 2012 |url-status=dead |accessdate=28 September 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2003\u201304 in English football]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablese/eng04.html 2003\u201304 FA Premier League Season at RSSSF]\n\n{{Premier League}}\n{{2003\u201304 in English football}}\n{{2003\u201304 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2003-04 FA Premier League}}\n[[Category:2003\u201304 FA Premier League| ]]\n[[Category:Premier League seasons]]\n[[Category:2003\u201304 in European association football leagues|Eng]]\n[[Category:2003\u201304 in English football leagues|1]]\n", "name_user": "KoSpades", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTop scorers", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2003%E2%80%9304_FA_Premier_League"}
